hondo717: |cp||at|lots to discuss. The play and defense are particularly noteworthy, but first the bidding, just to keep things orderly. The first few bids are fine. I think kia was somewhat aggressive making a takeout double.  He has the appropriate distribution, and he passed originally, so he doesn't have an opening hand, but having only 6 HCP in the unbid suits is a bit of a stretch.  Now, let me discuss support doubles and redoubles.|
